<br>
A riposted riposte would only mean -0- damage if it were perpetual (i.e. Enrage vs. Furious).   A riposte always ends in a swing, and that swing has the same chance to miss or hit as any regular swing.<br>
<br>
In other words...I swing at mob... he ripostes, it's a swing, and my defensive turn.  I'll either get hit, missed, dodge, parry, or riposte the return swing, no matter how the swing was generated (standard melee or riposte).<br>
<br>
If I get a double riposte, that simply means 2 return swings, both with the opportunity to hit, miss, be dodged, parried, riposted, or blocked.<br>
